    "name": "Stranded Particles Y-R",
    "profile": "STRANDED PARTICLES Y-R is no other than Spyros Anagnostou, songwriter/guitarist - multi-instrumentalist for a number of punk, new wave & psychedelic groups in Athens, Greece since the early 80s. Spyros has been going 'solo' since 1980, when he cut his first ever recording, \"The sun falls down\", in June of that year. On a par with his NOT 2 WITHOUT 3 days (1983-86), he continued to record psych folk material on a 'solo mode', as well as dark / new wave material destined to become part of NOT 2 WITHOUT 3's repertoire. \"Trying hard\" falls into that latter category.\r\n\r\nFor Spyros, other than his RED ELECTRONS psychedelic guise of 2006 onwards, there had been no other strictly solo release. That is up until now, that STRANDED PARTICLES Y-R's \"Trying hard\" marks the first ever release of Spyros' solo material from the mid 80s, penned while he was still writing and performing with NOT 2 WITHOUT 3. Indeed, \"Trying hard\" was one of his earliest new wave efforts, meant for his group's repertoire",
